The paper deals with random hypergraphs and their properties, which are typically studied in the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The concept of orientability is related to graph theory and combinatorics, which are also covered in cs.GT (Graph Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The applications mentioned in the abstract suggest that the paper may also have relevance to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and information theory (cs.IT).
